          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Security Engineering</h3><ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]"><li>Authentication and access control</li><li>Signal integrity verification</li><li>Tamper detection and rate limiting</li><li>Content validation before delivery</li></ul><p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] italic">Who can send content to a patient's brain?</p></div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-emerald-500">Ethical Governance</h3><ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]"><li>Informed consent protocols</li><li>Cognitive liberty protections</li><li>Mental privacy safeguards</li><li>Right to disconnect</li></ul><p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] italic">Who decides what a patient perceives?</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center reveal">
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-6">Every layer of this proposed pipeline requires both. Security without ethics is surveillance. Ethics without security is aspiration.</p>
          <p class="text-base text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-6">To build neural content delivery safely — to give a blind patient the ability to browse the web through a cortical prosthetic — requires security policies informed by neuroethics research. To get there, the science needs governance to do it responsibly.</p>
          <p class="text-base text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-6">A security engineer who spent a decade building SIEM infrastructure — detecting threats, classifying signals, writing detections — recognized the same architecture applies at the boundary between silicon and neuron. But the security framework alone isn't enough. The ethical governance to deploy it responsibly doesn't exist yet.</p>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold gradient-text mb-8">Neurosecurity needs neuroethics. Neuroethics needs neurosecurity.<br/>That's the bridge this research is building.</p>
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] tracking-[0.1em] mb-12">THEORETICAL VISION &middot; EARLY RESEARCH &middot; THE FRAMEWORKS ARE BEING BUILT NOW</p>
